ot the only Nobel laureate born in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Florida\" title=\"Florida\">Florida<\/a>.<\/p><p>This work helped further the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Big_Bang\" title=\"Big Bang\">Big Bang<\/a> theory of the universe using the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cosmic_Background_Explorer\" title=\"Cosmic Background Explorer\">Cosmic Background Explorer<\/a> (COBE) satellite.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/George_F._Smoot#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> According to the Nobel Prize committee, \"the COBE project can also be regarded as the starting point for <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cosmology\" title=\"Cosmology\">cosmology<\/a> as a precision science.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/George_F._Smoot#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Smoot donated his share of the Nobel Prize money, less travel costs, to a charitable foundation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/George_F._Smoot#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Currently Smoot is a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Professor\" title=\"Professor\">professor<\/a> of physics at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_California,_Berkeley\" title=\"University of California, Berkeley\">University of California, Berkeley<\/a>, senior scientist at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Lawrence_Berkeley_National_Laboratory\" title=\"Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory\">Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory<\/a>, and since 2010, a professor of physics at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paris_Diderot_University\" title=\"Paris Diderot University\">Paris Diderot University<\/a>, France. In 2003, he was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Einstein_Medal\" title=\"Einstein Medal\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Einstein Medal<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Oersted_Medal\" title=\"Oersted Medal\">Oersted Medal<\/a> in 2009.<\/p>","name":"George F. Smoot","place_of_birth":"Jacksonville, Florida, United States","place_of_death":null,"text":"George F. Smoot , Physics, 2006","year":2006.0}